        • extensionalPredicates

          Set<E> extensionalPredicates
          Leaf predicates are those that do not appear in the head of any rule. If a predicate is a leaf predicate, it should not be unfolded, they indicate stop points to get partial evaluations.

          Any atom that is not a leaf, and that cannot be unified with a rule (either cause of lack of MGU, or because of a rule for the predicate of the atom) is logically empty w.r.t. to the program.
